# AIUP — Alfresco extension development (Cursor)

You are working in a repository that follows **AIUP** (AI Unified Process) for Alfresco Content Services extensions.

## Mandatory first step

Before generating, editing, or reviewing Alfresco-related code (Java under Alfresco modules, `alfresco/module/**`, content models, web scripts, Share config, Spring Boot event listeners, `compose.yaml`, etc.), **read and follow** the project rules in **`AGENTS.md`** at the repository root. Treat `AGENTS.md` as the single source of truth for stack versions, layout, naming, forbidden patterns, and testing conventions.

## How AIUP commands map here

There are no Claude-style slash commands in Cursor. AIUP “commands” are Markdown specifications:

- **`commands/<name>.md`** — full procedure for `/requirements`, `/scaffold`, `/content-model`, and so on.  
  When the user asks to run an AIUP step, open the matching file (or use `@commands/<name>.md`) and execute the Markdown body; ignore Claude-only YAML front matter except as hints.

- **`.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`** — Cursor-native copies of validator skills and agent guidance (regenerate with `./scripts/build-cursor-skills.sh`). Also available under `skills/` for Claude Code.

- **`agents/*.md`** — source for agent skills; prefer the matching `.cursor/skills/` entry or `@agents/...` when useful.

When the user asks to run an AIUP step without naming a file, use the **`aiup-alfresco`** skill orchestrator or open `commands/<name>.md` directly.

## Output expectations

When an AIUP command requires file output, **create or update real files** in the repo; do not stop at a high-level summary unless the user only asked for a plan.

## Portable prompts

To get a single copy-paste prompt for Cursor Agent, from the repo root run:

`./scripts/aiup-command.sh render --agent cursor <command> [args...]`

See **`CURSOR.md`** for installation, workflows, hooks, and troubleshooting.
